B.a3E=new A.dj("source_craft","Craft","The character gains their powers from consumable creations that they make during combat. At the start of your turn, make a create check, on success gain 1 ingredient. When using an ability, the character must spend 1 ingredient, gaining its effects and a source of {Power} . For every 4 points of this source, the character gains 1 ingredient type from below, minimum 1. Whenever you spend an ingredient, the ingredients type effect is added to the abilities effect. You start each encounter with 1 ingredient of each type you know. Abilities of this source do not require an implement and do not gain any effects from implements, and you may create with 1 free hand. You cannot concentrate on the abilities of this source. When an ability would call for concentration, instead make a status check on the start of each of the target\u2019s turns, on failure the effect ends for the target.\n[Action] gain {Half Power} ingredients of your choice.\n[Reaction] When you fail a status effect check against a target within range 6, spend your reaction and an ingredient to cause the check to succeed instead.","After you succeed on a skill check, gain 1 craft and pick a skill check. You and your allies can use the craft to gain advantage on the check. You may do this up to {Half Crafting pts} each situation. You do not gain crafts for a check in which you used a craft.","{Power}",B.n2,!1,null,null,B.Wn,"{points / 4}",2035632383)
B.BW=new A.kA(6,"transformation")
B.a4h=new A.bp("Melee","When you Succeed on an attack or check using your action, target an enemy range 1 and deal {points d12} Damage. ")
B.a43=new A.bp("Ranged","When you Succeed on an attack or check using your action, targeting an enemy range 4 and deal {points d10} Damage.")
B.a45=new A.bp("Elusive","When you Succeed on an attack or check using your action, Your movement doesn\u2019t provoke attacks and you gain {points /2} Speed until the end of your turn.")
B.a4_=new A.bp("Barrier","When you Succeed on an attack or check using your action,Gain {points /2 d10} Shield and until the start of your next turn, allies range 2 may spend your shield when taking damage. On Problems, allies range 2 may spend your shield when taking damage until the start of your next turn.")
B.a4k=new A.bp("Regenerative","When you Succeed on an attack or check using your action, Heal {points /2 d6}.")
B.a3M=new A.bp("Armored","When you Succeed on an attack or check using your action, Gain a +1 to defense results and resistance to {points /3} defenses until the start of your next turn. When you pick this, pick the defenses. On Problems, you gain only the resistances.")
B.U8=s([B.a4h,B.a43,B.a45,B.a4_,B.a4k,B.a3M],t.AJ)
B.a3F=new A.dj("source_form","Form","The character gains their power through altering their form. Once per encounter, they may transform into their alternate form before they activate one of their form source powers and remain changed as long as they are concentrating. They may only use this source when concentrating on their form, using a source value of {Power}. While in a form, they may concentrate on up to {Power} additional effects. When they lose concentration on their form, they lose concentration on these additional effects.\nYou may have multiple different forms, each different form is considered a separate source, Having its own usage and only being activatable when in the corresponding form. You may be concentrating on multiple forms at the same time, at the start of your turn select one of your forms to use its size, composition and defense class until your next turn. When concentrating on multiple forms, you may use any of those forms abilities regardless of which forms size you select. When concentrating on multiple forms, your extra forms do not grant you the ability to concentrate on extra effects per form.","Evenly divide the skills between your form and out of form. When you are in your form you have advantage on those skills and disadvantage on the other skills. Likewise when out of your form. When you succeed on a skill with disadvantage you change form. At the start of a situation, choose whether you are in your form.","{Power}",B.BW,!1,null,null,B.U8,"{1}",4288423856)
B.a3B=new A.dj("source_gadgets","Gadgets","The character gains their powers from created objects. Every combat feature is a unique object or a part in another unique object, that can appear as anything but has the properties of a single Implement selected when you take the feature. When you use the gadget, you have a source value of {Power + 2}. You may use the gadget once, then you must fix the gadget to use it again. If multiple features are in the same object, each feature can be used and fixed independently.\nFix: [Action] fix all of your Gadgets.\nJerryRig: [Reaction] During your or allies turn, you may spend your reaction and fix 1 gadget.","For each of your gadgets, You may gain advantage or +1 on results on a skill check. You may not do this again with this gadget until you either make a skill check with disadvantage or -1 to results.","{Power + 2}",B.n2,!1,null,null,B.fY,null,4294963574)
B.a3G=new A.dj("source_granted_power","Granted Power","The character gets their features from a powerful entity. For each point of features of this source they may gain 1 use of any of the features of this source. They regain all uses after each encounter. Your source value is {Power +1}.","You have {Half Points} blessings. When you fail a skill check, you may pay 1 blessing to reroll. At the end of a situation or combat encounter, regain all your blessings.","{Power + 1}",B.BS,!0,null,null,B.fY,null,4291937513)
B.BU=new A.kA(3,"heat")
B.a4d=new A.bp("Shield","Target you and allies range {Power}, and Gain {half points d6} shield.")
B.a4f=new A.bp("Burning","Target all enemies range {Power} and give them {half points d6} Burn vs Dex.")
B.a4j=new A.bp("Growing","Each time you overload, increase the damage done by all attacks of this overload by 1d6, to a max bonus of {Power + points /3 d6}.")
B.a46=new A.bp("Warp"," target you and allies range {Power} and teleport each target to a free space within {Half points +1}.")
B.WH=s([B.a4d,B.a4f,B.a4j,B.a46],t.AJ)
B.a3H=new A.dj("source_heat","Heat","The character gains their power through a slowly growing process, like a steam engine, or channeling spirit, or eating a big sandwich. Whenever you use an ability of this source, you gain 1 heat up to {Power + 1} and then do the ability using your heat as the source. When you would gain a heat but are at the max, you gain an overheat effect, and after you perform the ability, set your heat to 0. You pick the overheat effect when you pick the feature. Each overheat effect is a separate source. Features of the same overheat effect share heat, and you track each overheat effects heat levels separately.","During a situation, before making a roll you may warm up making the check with a -1 to the results. After warming up, for the rest of the situation you make that skill check with a +1 to results.","{1}",B.BU,!1,null,"{Power + 1}",B.WH,"{1}",4293874512)
B.BT=new A.kA(1,"resource")
B.a3C=new A.dj("source_intuitive_magic","Intuitive Magic","The caster can freely cast their magic. They have {2 * Power * intuitive magic points} Max MP, regaining half after each encounter. They must spend at least 1 MP and may spend up to {Power +Half Power} MP when using a feature as the Source Value.\n\nRitual Magic: [Reaction] When an ally within 3 spaces Uses a feature of a Magical Source, You may spend your reaction and give them up to {Power} of your MP to trigger their feature. The Ally loses {Their Vitality d6} Health per MP given. This Health loss cannot be reduced in any way, and the target may not continue to gain MP once they have brought their health below zero. You may use Ritual Magic from your corps, but you must pay 1 MP to do it, and you may target an ally in range {4*Power}.","You may spend 1 mp to gain advantage on a skill or defense check. If multiple characters are making the same check, you may spend 1 MP per character to give them advantage. When you finish a situation, regain {Intuitive magic pts} MP.","1",B.BT,!0,"MP","{2 * Power * points}",B.fY,null,4293943954)
B.f7=new A.kA(2,"resourceWithSelection")
B.a41=new A.bp("Flow","During your turn, You may spend 1 Ki point to Dodge, Run or Retreat after the ability.")
B.a3T=new A.bp("Flurry","During your turn, You may spend 1 Ki Point to make 1 Melee Attack targeting an enemy range 1. On success, deal {Power d6}. Choose the defense targeted when you pick this.")
B.a4a=new A.bp("Restore","During your turn, You may spend 1 Ki Point to gain {Half Level d12} Regeneration.")
B.a3S=new A.bp("Breath","Before you would make an Int, Wis, or Cha defense, you may pay 1 Ki to gain advantage on the roll.")
B.a3J=new A.bp("Meditative","After you fail a concentration, spend 1 ki point and succeed instead.")
B.a3L=new A.bp("Present","You fail with a ki attack, you may spend a ki point to reroll the attack.")
B.Wx=s([B.a41,B.a3T,B.a4a,B.a3S,B.a3J,B.a3L],t.AJ)
B.a3w=new A.dj("source_ki","Ki","The character gains their powers from controlling their body's energy called ki. For each point spent on this source, the character gains 2 ki points, regaining all after every encounter. A character can activate their features using 1 ki point using a source of {Half Power} and they may trigger one of their ki effects. For every 2 points spent on this source, gain 1 of the below options.","Before you make a skill check, you may pay 2 ki to gain advantage or if you are proficient in the skill you may pay 1 point to gain a +1 to the die result. You regain all your ki points at the start of a situation or combat encounter.","{Half Power}",B.f7,!1,"Ki","{2 * points}",B.Wx,"{points / 2}",4291611852)
B.a3P=new A.bp("Buzzed","Gain {Vice + Vitality} shield up to the max of {Points}.")
B.a3Z=new A.bp("Angry","This round, you deal extra damage equal to your concentration roll on all attacks or damaging status checks.")
B.a49=new A.bp("Friendly","You may make a status check vs cha, on success, pull an enemy {Half Vice + Vitality} up to the number of points spent on this source. You may instead target an ally and force them to move the same distance as you would have pulled an enemy.")
B.a44=new A.bp("Attacks and Skills","You and all creatures in adjacent to your specter have a -1 to success on attacks and skills")
B.a3X=new A.bp("Defenses","You and all creatures in adjacent to your specter have a -1 to success on defenses.")
B.ag1=s([B.a44,B.a3X],t.AJ)
B.a3N=new A.bp("Regretful","Target a free space within {Half Vice + Half Vitality} up to your Vice Pts and summon a specter of your regrets that last until you activate this again or die.\nSpecters block their space, use your defenses, and you take half damage dealt to your specter ignoring shield and resistance.")
B.WL=s([B.a3P,B.a3Z,B.a49,B.a3N],t.AJ)
B.a3z=new A.dj("source_vice","Vice","At the start of your turn, you may consume your vice losing {2 * Vitality} health and gaining {Power} vice. You may have up to {2* power} vice and it is lost at the end of the encounter. You can spend up to {Power} vice as the source value when you use an ability of this source, you may pay the vice health cost again to not pay the vice.","Choose either Convince or Conceal. You may take your vice during a situation to gain a +1 to results of all skills other than the selected skill and disadvantage on the selected skill.","{Power}",B.f7,!1,"Vice","{2 * power}",B.WL,"{1}",4290190364)
B.a4g=new A.bp("Sprint","During your turn, you may pay stamina to move extra spaces. You move up to 2 spaces further for each stamina spent. This doesn't alter your speed. Whenever you are under an effect that reduces your speed, you move 1 space per stamina instead.")
B.a3W=new A.bp("Dodge Roll","Before rolling a defense, you may spend {Vitality} stamina to gain advantage on the defense, After the attack dash 1 space.")
B.a3O=new A.bp("Follow through","On success with an attack that deals damage, you may spend up to {Half Power} stamina to deal 1d6 extra damage per stamina spent.")
B.a3Q=new A.bp("Leap","[Reaction] During your turn or at the end of an alley\u2019s turn, [Reaction] and Pay up to {Vitality} stamina, and dash to a free space within 2 * paid stamina.")
B.a3Y=new A.bp("Stretch","Once per ability, you may pay 1 stamina to increase your range by 1.")
B.WV=s([B.a4g,B.a3W,B.a3O,B.a3Q,B.a3Y],t.AJ)
B.a3D=new A.dj("source_stamina","Stamina","The character gains their power through their physical endurance and strength. The character starts with their max stamina, and regains all stamina at the end of the encounter. When they use a feature of this source, they may spend up to {Power} stamina, using the spent stamina as the source value. At the end of the round, if they haven't spent stamina this round, they rest and gain {Power + Vitality} Stamina. For every 4 pts worth of combat features of the stamina source, gain 1 of the below abilities. You always know at least 1.","You may pay {half power} stamina to reroll a skill or defense with a +1 to the result. You start the next encounter without this stamina.","{Power}",B.f7,!1,"Stamina","{Power * points}",B.WV,"{points / 4}",4281236786)
B.BV=new A.kA(4,"time")
B.a3x=new A.dj("source_time","Time","The character gains their power through altering time or predicting the future. After each encounter, you may select your chronomancy from 1 to {half time feature points}. Your time source is {power - chronomancy}. At the start of a situation, Roll and record {Chronomancy +1} attacks and {Chronomancy +1} skills you are proficient in. When you use this source you use one of your applicable chronomancy results, then roll a replacement result. Whenever you have advantage or disadvantage, select 1 result then roll the extra check. If you gain a reroll, reroll as normal. When you change your chronomancy at the end of an encounter, you pick which results are lost, and you only make new rolls for gained chronomancy. You may use an Implement gaining any implement effects. If you do, you require that type of implement to use the feature.","Roll and track {Half Chronomancy} results for {Half Chronomancy} defenses and {Half Chronomancy} skills you aren\u2019t proficient in. Prediction: Before a creature makes a check, [Reaction] and give them one of your applicable chronomancy results for that check as if you had used it.","{power - chronomancy}",B.BV,!0,"Chronomancy",null,B.fY,null,4289773253)
B.a3I=new A.bp("Penetration","Pay 1 Psi Points and your ability ignores resistance.")
B.a3K=new A.bp("Drain","On Success, Pay up to {Half power} Additional Psi Points, to deal 1d6 extra damage and gain an equal amount of shield per Psi Point.")
B.a48=new A.bp("Focus","pay 1 Psi Points, and attacks ignore advantage, disadvantage, -1 and +1 to results for the attack and defenses caused by the attack.")
B.a4e=new A.bp("Distant","Pay 1 Psi Points and double the range of the ability or if the ability targets an area, increase the area size and range by 1.")
B.a4i=new A.bp("Phasing","pay 1 Psi point, and your movement doesn't prove attacks of opportunity and you ignore difficult terrain.),")
B.Vd=s([B.a3I,B.a3K,B.a48,B.a4e,B.a4i],t.AJ)
B.a3y=new A.dj("source_psionics","Psionics","The character uses their mind to alter reality. They have {2 * Power * Psionics points} Max Psi Points, regaining half after each encounter. When using a feature, They must spend at least 1 Psi Points and may spend up to {Power} Psi Points as the Source Value, and they may trigger one of their psi powers. They pick {Total Psi Pts /4} psi powers.\nPenetration, Drain, Focus, Distant, Phasing (see docs for effects).","You may spend 1 Psi Point to gain advantage on a skill or defense check. If a character you can see is making a skill that you have proficiency in, you may spend 1 Psi points and that character rolls using your skill rather than their own. When you finish a situation, regain {Psionics pts} Psi Points.","Psi Points Spent",B.f7,!0,"Psi Points","{2 * Power * points}",B.Vd,"{points / 4}",4291611852)
