s($,"b82","JF",()=>{var q=null
return A.b([A.aA("when you use your aside, the target forgets about your allies who spoke previously.",q,"epic_background_aside","Epic Aside","background_aside",B.az),A.aA("{Half Level} times as a situation, you can have your assistant make a check related to your background using a d12.",q,"epic_background_assistant","Epic Assistant","background_assistant",B.az),A.aA("you gain a use of bad ping every situation in addition to your situation roll.",q,"epic_background_bad_ping","Epic Bad Ping","background_bad_ping",B.az),A.aA("the first time you would use supply in each situation, have someone provide you what you needed and don't spend supply.",q,"epic_background_charitable","Epic Charitable","background_charitable",B.az),A.aA("every situation you may ask each person a yes no question that must be answered truthfully.",q,"epic_background_detect_lies","Epic Detect Lies","background_detect_lies",B.az),A.aA("every situation, you may make yourself appear as an advertisement, concealing your identity to passersby.",q,"epic_background_explosive_ads","Epic Explosive Ads","background_explosive_ads",B.az),A.aA("when you use your flash smoke you teleport a short distance. Gain 1 usage every situation.",q,"epic_background_flash_smoke","Epic Flash Smoke","background_flash_smoke",B.az),A.aA("once during the situation, you may have the owner, manager or authority be a casual friend of yours.",q,"epic_background_friends","Epic Friends","background_friends",B.az),A.aA("once per situation, you may hide your allies in your shadow. They cannot target abilities nor be targeted until they exit your shadow. They may remain hidden in your bodies shadow if you die.",q,"epic_background_friends_in_the_shadows","Epic Friends in the Shadows","background_friends_in_the_shadows",B.az),A.aA("at the start of every situation, gain the use of gremlin.",q,"epic_background_gremlin","Epic Gremlin","background_gremlin",B.az),A.aA("Once every situation, you may make someone so irritated, that they are stunned with temporary anger and are unable to do anything.",q,"epic_background_irritation","Epic Irritation","background_irritation",B.az),A.aA("when you pocket sand, you also turn into a cloud of sand for a minute. Gain 1 usage each situation. While sand, you cannot be targeted, you can fly and you can move through anything a cloud could. The sand condenes after a minute and reforms into your body",q,"epic_background_pocket_sand","Epic Pocket Sand","background_pocket_sand",B.az),A.aA("your allies can use your quick talker rerolls. Start every situation with {Level /3} usages.",q,"epic_background_quick_talker","Epic Quick Talker","background_quick_talker",B.az),A.aA("gain offline chat usage every encounter. Your allies gain a +1 to the results of their next skill check after an offline chat",q,"epic_background_offline_chat","Epic Offline Chat","background_offline_chat",B.az),A.aA("you may swap any persons or objects instead of scorching. Gain {Level /3} usages of scooch.",q,"epic_background_scooch","Epic Scooch","background_scooch",B.az),A.aA("once during a situation, you may make an object you can see appear in your hand.",q,"epic_background_snatch","Epic Snatch","background_snatch",B.az),A.aA("Supporter forum: whenever you make a study check, you can ask your supports to check using {1d20}.",q,"epic_background_subscriber_poll","Epic Subscriber Poll","background_subscriber_poll",B.az),A.aA("you may move through walls. The denser and thicker the material, the longer it takes.",q,"epic_background_through","Epic Through","background_through",B.az),A.aA("once per situation, you may ask for a clear explanation of the current situation.",q,"epic_background_understanding","Epic Understanding","background_understanding",B.az),A.aA("you always have wall walker, when you trigger wall walker with a situation roll. This situation, {Level /3} times, you may teleport to a location you can see.",q,"epic_background_wall_walker","Epic Wall Walker","background_wall_walker",B.az),A.aA(q,"when you perform [Action], you may have it instead target a 1 space radius and have the ability trigger at the end of the round instead. If you do, increase the damage by {Half Level d10} and increase any healing or shielding by {Half level d10}.","epic_method_artillery","Epic Artillery","method_artillery",B.a0),A.aA(q,"you may use the location of any enemy you see as the origin for targeting [actions] and [Reaction]. If you do and succeed on an attack, you apply your body hacker effect to the origin enemy until the start of your next turn.","epic_method_body_hacker","Epic Body Hacker","method_body_hacker",B.a0),A.aA(q,"Burst: When you Succeed on an attack using your action, Target each enemy within 1 of any targets of the action. Deal {Half Level d6} damage to all targets. Do not target anything more than once. The original targets are not affected unless they are in range of another original target.\nWhen you use your [Action] to [Run], [Retreat], [Ready], or [Jump], You may make an attack roll, and on success trigger your burst using yourself as the origin. You may have the burst trigger before or after you perform the action.","epic_method_burst_mage","Epic Burst Mage","method_burst_mage",B.a0),A.aA(q,"You gain 1 snack or meal at the start of your turn. When you use an item interaction to give an ally a snack, you may target an ally range {Half Level}. When you or allies would overheal from snacks or meals, gain the unused healing as a shield. You may make single target melee attacks as ranged attacks range 3/6.","epic_method_chef","Epic Chef","method_chef",B.a0),A.aA(q,"You dash instead of moving. The first time you dash through an enemy each turn, deal {Half Level} damage and reduce their speed by {Half Level}.","epic_method_concrete_surfer","Epic Concrete Surfer","method_concrete_surfer",B.a0),A.aA(q,"whenever you miss with an attack, gain 1d6 extra death damage on all attacks until the end of the situation, to a max of {Level} d6. When you miss and are at max trigger your deathweaver instead. Whenever an enemy range {Half Level} dies, gain {1d6} as if you had missed. You start each situation with {power} d6","epic_method_death_weaver","Epic Death Weaver","method_death_weaver",B.a0),A.aA(q,"you gain 1 drone at the start of your turn. When you use a drone, target yourself and allies range 2 of the drone space and give them {Half Level d8} shield.","epic_method_drone","Epic Drone","method_drone",B.a0),A.aA(q,"whenever you hit a creature with an attack, set 1 space under them on fire. While on fire, the first time a creature starts or enters the fire during their turn, they gain {Level/3} d6 Burn. The fires may be put out as if they were burn but using any applicable skill.","epic_method_fire_weaver","Epic Fire Weaver","method_fire_weaver",B.a0),A.aA(q,"end of round, if you damaged an enemy this round, heal {Half Level d6}. Whenever you make an attack, you may roll and take up to {Half level dice} worth of damage to add the same dice as bonus damage on the attack. You pick the dice. If you do not survive the cost, the attack succeeds before you die.","epic_method_hemomancer","Epic Hemomancer","method_hemomancer",B.a0),A.aA(q,"When an enemy ends its turn with Cold from you, it takes {1d12} damage for each Cold it has. Whenever a creature fails a check to unfreeze when it was frozen by you, deal {their Vitality d12} to them.","epic_method_ice_weaver","Epic Ice Weaver","method_ice_weaver",B.a0),A.aA(q,"you may target your [actions] and [Reactions] using any allies or willing creatures you can see.\nWhen you succeed on a check using your Action, heal 1 ally range 4 {half level d8} HP.","epic_method_life_weaver","Epic Life Weaver","method_life_weaver",B.a0),A.aA(q,"whenever you succeed in attacking an enemy, knock the targets prone. If they are already prone, deal {Half Level d10} lighting damage.","epic_method_lightning_weaver","Epic Lightning Weaver","method_lightning_weaver",B.a0),A.aA(q,"whenever you succeed in attacking an enemy using your [Action] or [Reaction], Make a Melee Attack vs Str or Dex targeting 1 enemy range 1. On Success, Deal {Level d6} damage.","epic_method_martial_artist","Epic Martial Artist","method_martial_artist",B.a0),A.aA(q,"when you make an [Action], create a wall of dead in a free space range 6 and target the ability from the walls location. The wall lasts until the start of your next turn and is treated as a wall. When an enemy starts adjacent to the wall or becomes adjacent for the first time during its turn, deal {Half Level d10}. When you make a [Reaction], make a pile of dead in a free space range 6 and target the ability from the pile. The pile counts as a barrier and lasts until the start of your next turn. When an enemy starts adjacent to the wall or becomes adjacent for the first time during its turn, deal {Half Level d6}. You and your allies may consume an adjacent wall or pile as a [Reaction], destroying it and healing {Half Level d12} for a wall and {Half Level d6} for a pile. Do not generate a pile for this destroy reaction.","epic_method_necromancer","Epic Necromancer","method_necromancer",B.a0),A.aA(q,"You do not provoke attacks and may move through enemy spaces. You always have otherworldly. When you trigger Otherworldly from a situation roll, you may pull enemies you can see up to {Power} spaces and next round, you and your allies have +1 to defense results for abilities caused by enemies who have been damaged by your otherworldly Aura.","epic_method_otherworldly","Epic Otherworldly","method_otherworldly",B.a0),A.aA(q,"you gain resistance to all damage and may teleport up to your speed instead of walking.","epic_method_phasing","Epic Phasing","method_phasing",B.a0),A.aA(q,"whenever you succeed on an attack or status check, give the target { Level /3} d10 Burn. Whenever you spend your action to do a skill, also gain a poison as if you had triggered Poisoner.","epic_method_poisoner","Epic Poisoner","method_poisoner",B.a0),A.aA(q,"whenever an ally within {Half Level} is damaged by an attack, you can take that damage instead. When you lose shield and protection as a result of taking damage, for each 1 lost reduce the damage by 2. This has no effect on abilities that have you pay, or loss shields.","epic_method_protector","Epic Protector","method_protector",B.a0),A.aA(q,"After you attack an enemy who didn\u2019t have any rainbow charges, give them a rainbow charge. Whenever you trigger a rainbow charge, you may heal an ally within range 6 of you {Half Level d6}.","epic_method_rainbow_weaver","Epic Rainbow Weaver","method_rainbow_weaver",B.a0),A.aA(q,"End of round, you may trigger Restorer in addition to your trait roll. For each time a character is targeted by Restorer after the first, they also gain 1d6 Regeneration.","epic_method_restorer","Epic Restorer","method_restorer",B.a0),A.aA(q,"your smite targets enemies range 2 of the target. At the end of the round, you smite in addition to your situation roll.","epic_method_smite","Epic Smite","method_smite",B.a0),A.aA(q,"Start of turn gain 1 training. You may also spend 1 training when an ally range {Level} makes an attack to give that attack advantage.","epic_method_soldier","Epic Soldier","method_soldier",B.a0),A.aA(q,"once per encounter during your turn, target an enemy you can see, pull them to an adjacent to you, gain soul shards equal to the number of turns the target has. Gain {Soul Shards d12} shield and deal that much damage to the target and each enemy adjacent to you.","epic_method_soul_adorn","Epic Soul Adorn","method_soul_adorn",B.a0),A.aA(q,"Once per Encounter, at the end of your turn, target an enemy you can see. You become untargetable by allies and enemies, and enter the target. On the start of your next turn, gain soul shards equal to the number of turns the target has, heal {Soul Shards d10} and deal the same amount as damage to the target. Then place yourself in a free space adjacent to the target.","epic_method_soul_feaster","Epic Soul Feaster","soul_feaster",B.a0),A.aA(q,"Once each encounter, target an enemy you can see. Gain soul shards equal to the number of turns the target has, the target takes {Soul Shards d12} damage ignoring shield and resistance. For the rest of the encounter gain +{soul shards} range on all attacks.","epic_method_soul_reaper","Epic Soul Reaper","method_soul_reaper",B.a0),A.aA(q,"when you succeed on an attack or status check, give the target spores. At the end of the round, every spore blooms, target each creature within 2 of a spore carrier, targeting nothing more than once, enemies take {half level d6} damage and allies heal equal to the damage.","epic_method_spore_spreader","Epic Spore Spreader","method_spore_spreader",B.a0),A.aA(q,"You may teleport your speed instead of moving. Once per turn, When you teleport, you may bring an adjacent creature to you to a free space adjacent to your destination. After you are attacked, teleport {half level} spaces.","epic_method_stride","Epic Stride","method_stride",B.a0),A.aA(q,"You may target your attacks from your summons\u2019 locations. At the end of your turn, If you have less than {Half Level} summons, You may place a summon into a free space range 6.","epic_method_summoner","Epic Summoner","method_summoner",B.a0),A.aA(q,"when you succeed on an attack with advantage or have at least 1 ally to the target, give them {Half level} d6 bleed and until the start of your next turn, you do not provoke attacks.","epic_method_unfair_attacker","Epic Unfair Attacker","method_unfair_attacker",B.a0),A.aA(q,"before or after you do an [Action] make a weapon attack.","epic_method_warrior","Epic Warrior","method_warrior",B.a0),A.aA(q,"when you succeed on attacks until the start of your next turn, enemies targeted take {Half level d6} bonus damage from attacks and have their speed reduced by half. When you succeed on a check to heal Allies, the targeted ally gains {Half Level d6} shield and deal {Half level d6} extra water damage on attacks until the start of your next turn.","epic_method_water_weaver","Epic Water Weaver","method_water_weaver",B.a0),A.aA(q,"when you make a ranged attack you may target from any weed. When you make a melee attack, you may target it from each weed targeting no enemy more than once. At the end of each of your turns, turn 1 free space into weeds.","epic_method_weed_weaver","Epic Weed Weaver","method_weed_weaver",B.a0),A.aA(q,"whenever you succeed on an attack or status check, you may force dash you or the target up to {Half Level} spaces.","epic_method_wind_weaver","Epic Wind Weaver","method_wind_weaver",B.a0),A.aA("At the start of every situation, gain {Innate Feature pts /3} Rerolls.","Once a Round, on your turn, you may take an extra action. You may do this {Innate Feature pts /3} times each encounter.","epic_source_innate","Epic Innate","source_innate",B.ba),A.aA("When your allies fail skills you may have your companions make the check instead. Whenever you gain downtime, gain 1 extra.","Once per turn, when 1 of your companions would use their [Minion], instead have them activate one of their companions.","epic_source_companion","Epic Companion","source_companion",B.ba),A.aA("You can always make a craft after a skill check. When you roll a defense, you may use a craft to gain advantage if the defense is the same stat attribute as the skill.","Pick 1 ingredient effect as a secret ingredient, adding its effect whenever you use ingredients. You may not benefit from an ingredient effect twice. If you pick an ingredient that you already have, gain a new ingredient.\nBefore an ally within {Half Level} activates an Ability, you may spend 1 or 2 ingredients to give their ability the benefit of the ingredient effects. Allies do not get your secret ingredient bonus but you may have any ingredient provide the secret ingredients effect instead.","epic_source_craft","Epic Crafting","source_craft",B.ba),A.aA("Your allies in the situation with you may also adopt your Adventuring form, gaining the same benefits. At the start of every situation, you gain 2 skill reroll and gain 1 addition reroll for each ally who adopts your form.","Pick an aspect, choosing any of the form ability options. When in your form, when allies who are within {Half Level} spaces of you spend their [Action] and succeed on an attack, you may apply your aspect effect to them. When you Succeed on a Reaction apply your aspect effect.","epic_source_form","Epic Form","source_form",B.ba),A.aA("You may use each of your gadgets twice before needing to repair them.","You may use each of your gadgets 2 times before needing to repair them. When you repair a gadget, replenish both usages. When you use a gadget, you may expend an additional usage of this gadget or a usage of another gadget to gain a +2 Source mod to the ability.","epic_source_gadgets","Epic Gadgets","source_gadgets",B.ba),A.aA("When you pay a blessing, give one creature you can see 1 skill reroll. If you give an enemy 1 usage you regain 1 use of your blessing.","After you make your situation roll, You may pay 1 usage of granted power to pick 1 of your methods instead. Whenever you would die, you may spend a usage of granted power, to instead become full HP. [Action], you may spend a usage of granted power to target an ally you can see and give them their Max Shield. [Action], you may spend a usage of granted power and target an adjacent ally's body who died this round. Immediately respawn the ally there, setting their HP to half.","epic_source_granted_power","Epic Granted Power","source_granted_power",B.ba),A.aA("After you have warmed up a skill, your allies in the situation with you also gain the +1 bonus to results of that skill.","You gain an extra overheat effect called your Epic Overheat, whenever you gain 1 heat, your Epic Overheat gains 2 heat. Every time you trigger your Epic Overheat, gain a +1 source mod to heat abilities for the rest of the encounter, up to a max of {Level/3}. Your epic overheat may be an overheat effect you have already chosen.","epic_source_heat","Epic Heat","source_heat",B.ba),A.aA("When you spend MP on a skill, gain +1 to the result. When you spend MP to give allies advantage, they gain a +1 to the result.","Whenever you succeed on an attack or status check caused by an ability you spent MP on, you may spend up to {Half Level} MP to trigger one of the below effects using that spent MP. Do not include the MP spent to trigger the ability.\nDeal {MP d6} damage to an enemy within {MP}.\nTarget an ally range {MP} and either heal {MP d6} or gain {MP d6} shield.\nTarget 1 creature range {MP} and force them to dash {MP}","epic_source_intuitive_magic","Epic Intuitive Magic","source_intuitive_magic",B.ba),A.aA("You and your allies can use prepared skill spells to reroll skill checks of the prepared skill. When you finish a situation, Regain {Prepared Magic pts /3} MP.","Once per round, After you use your [Action] to use a prepared magic feature, you may use a multicast to perform another prepared magic feature using an [Action] that is a different combat feature than the original action. You may use multicast {Prepared Magic pts / 3} times every encounter.","epic_source_prepared_magic","Epic Prepared Magic","source_prepared_magic",B.ba),A.aA("You may pay 1 ki to reroll skills you are proficient in, and you may pay 2 ki to reroll skills you are not proficient in.","Gain a +1 bonus to your source for all your ki abilities. When you spend your reaction, you may pay 1 ki to regain your reaction. When you fail a defense, you may spend 1 ki to reroll.","epic_source_ki","Epic Ki","source_ki",B.ba),A.aA("When you fail a save or defense, you may pay {3 * Vitality} Health and reroll with advantage.","When you are at or over {Power} vice, you add +1 to the source of your vice abilities, your vice cost increases to { Vitality d6}, and at the end of your turn, you heal {Vitality d6} after Bleed & burn and you must pick a different vice effect than the last round.","epic_source_vice","Epic Vice","source_vice",B.ba),A.aA("Whenever you make a check and don\u2019t spend stamina, gain 1 stamina.","When you succeed on an attack that costs stamina, regain half the spent Stamina. Whenever you succeed on a defense, regain {Power / 3} stamina points. You may spend up to {Power +2} stamina on features.","epic_source_stamina","Epic Stamina","source_stamina",B.ba),A.aA("You may mutate {Mutation Pts} times per situation. Allies in the situation may use your skill mutation to mutate themselves for the remainder of the encounter.","Before activating a Mutation, you may change which upgrades that mutation has. For 1 of your mutations, you may have 1 extra upgrade. [Action] Reorganize: You may lose any number of your current mutations, and regain evolution points equal to their cost.","epic_source_mutation","Epic Mutation","source_mutation",B.ba),A.aA("","Roll and track {Half Chronomancy} results for {Half Chronomancy} defenses and {Half Chronomancy} skills you aren't proficient in. Prediction: Before a creature makes a check, [Reaction] and give them one of your applicable chronomancy results for that check as if you had used it.","epic_source_time","Epic Time","source_time",B.ba),A.aA("When you or an ally you can see would make a skill check, you may spend 2 Psi points to have them use your check or use a willing ally you can see skill check instead.","You may concentrate on {Level /3} additional psy abilities, when you lose concentration on one you lose contraction on all. When you succeed on an attack, deal 1d12 extra damage for each ability you are concentrating on.\nYou may spend 1 Psi point when you activate a psi ability to target the ability from a free space within {Half total Psi Pts} or from the space of any ally.\nWhen an ally who is within {Half total Psionic points} uses an ability, you may pay Psi points to apply one of your Psi abilities to the attack.","epic_source_psionics","Epic Psionics","source_psionics",B.ba),A.aA("Work Blend: Select 4 skills when to take this. While high you have a +1 to skill results of the selected skills. You always have a -1 to skill results for the skills you didn\u2019t select.","While high, you resist all damage but have disadvantage on defense checks. You gain a bonus based on the addiction mod.\nQuick: While high, gain {Level / 3} Speed.\nStrong: While high, deal {Level / 3 d6} Extra damage on all attacks.\nHomemade: While high, As a [Action] You may make a create check. On Success, make {Power} Drugs and give them to an ally range 4. Your allies may consume Drugs as an item interaction to gain Resistance to all damage until the start of their next turn.","epic_addict","Epic Addict","trait_addict",B.ay),A.aA("When you succeed on a skill check without a bonus, +1 to result, a reroll, or advantage, gain 1 confidence reroll. When you fail a skill, lose all confidence rerolls.","When you Succeed on an attack, Roll and deal your confidence as bonus damage to the attack's targets, Then gain {1d6} confidence. When you succeed on a defense, Roll and gain your confidence as shield, Then gain {1d6} Confidence. When you fail an attack or defense, lose all your confidence.","epic_confidence","Epic Confidence","trait_confidence",B.ay),A.aA("If you complete a situation and failed at least 1 check, gain 1 downtime.","You have resistance to damage caused by characters who, since your last turn, you have not targeted with an attack or status check. You have advantage on concentration checks caused by damage you resisted via epic distractible.","epic_distractible","Epic Distractible","trait_distractible",B.ay),A.aA("during a situation, you may reroll a skill with a +1 to the result if you forget a skill for the rest of the situation. If you see forced to make a forgotten skill, you fail automatically.","On the start of your turn, target 1 enemy and 1 ally. The targets may not target you with any of their abilities until the start of your next turn nor may you target them. If the enemy has multiple turns, choose 1 turn to be forgotten.\nOnce each encounter, When you activate an ability, you may forget one of your combat features for the rest of the encounter. You gain a source mod of {Half the features pts} for the remainder of the encounter. Mutations instead may pay up to 3 evolution points instead, gaining a source mod of {Half amount paid} for the remainder of the encounter.","epic_forgetful","Epic Forgetful","trait_forgetful",B.ay),A.aA("Before each skill check, flip a coin, Heads you have advantage and gain a reroll, tails disadvantage. You may not have more than {Half Level} rerolls.","At the Start of your turn, Roll 2d6. If you don\u2019t roll a 7, Gain {Level d6} Shield and gain {Half Level d8} Bonus damage on all attacks. If you roll a 7, you are stunned.","epic_gambler","Epic Gambler","trait_gambler",B.ay),A.aA("Up to {Half Level} times per situation, your allies may use your skill rating when making a skill check.","When an ally within 4 takes damage, you may give them resistance to the damage, and you take the same amount of damage. When you target an ally with an effect, you may give them any amount of your HP and Shield. When you use either effect, at The start of the target's next turn, they heal {Half Level d6}.","epic_giving","Epic Giving","trait_giving",B.ay),A.aA("You have advantage on checks to assist your allies.","Allies adjacent to you have advantage on attacks and skill checks.","epic_helpful","Epic Helpful","trait_helpful",B.ay),A.aA("Up to {Half Level} Times per situation, you may reroll a skill check by making a different skill check.","Once during your turn, Up to {Half Level} times each encounter, When you fail with using your [Action], you may activate a different feature instead. Up to {Half Level} times each encounter, when you fail a defense, you may reroll using a different defense.","epic_impulsive","Epic Impulsive","trait_impulsive",B.ay),A.aA("when you fail a defense other than dex and have your keepsake. You may reroll the defense.","If you or an ally you can see would die and you have your keepsake, they instead set their HP to half. You may do this {Level /3} times per situation. If your keepsake is destroyed, any characters saved by it make a Vitality defense and die on a failure.","epic_keepsake","Epic Keepsake","trait_keepsake",B.ay),A.aA("you have {Half Level} backup plans. For each backup plan, pick 1 character, and a skill. When the character fails at the selected skill, reveal your backup plan and have another character make the skill check with a +1 to the results.","you may make {Half Level} Plans. Before the encounter, for each plan, predict a character, a round, and a type of check (attack, defense, skill). If your prediction is correct, you may trigger the prediction, the named character gains the following effect based on the type of action.\nAttack, gain advantage on the attack and deal {Half Level d6} extra damage.\nDefense: gain advantage on the defense and {Half Level d6} shield, the target cannot be killed by the attack, if they would be killed they are set to half HP instead.\nSkill: the target has advantage and a +1 to the results.","epic_planner","Epic Planner","trait_planner",B.ay),A.aA("You have a +1 bonus to results and advantage on defenses. You have disadvantage on skills you aren\u2019t proficient in.","Impenetrable anxiety: When a character targets you with an ability, you may no longer be a target by the attack or ability until the start of your next turn. You may do this up to {Half Level} times per encounter.\nWhen you Succeed on an attack, if no enemy is adjacent, Deal {Half Level - remaining Usages of Impenetrable Anxiety d12} extra damage. If an enemy is adjacent, Reduce your damage by that amount instead.","epic_nervous","Epic Nervous","trait_nervous",B.ay),A.aA("when an ally fails a skill, you may attempt the skill instead. You may do this {Half level} times each situation.","You gain {Half Level} bonus reactions at the start of a combat situation that last until the end of the situation. You may use these reactions as reactions whenever they could be triggered, you still have 1 reaction per turn as normal.","epic_reactive","Epic Reactive","trait_reactive",B.ay),A.aA("you gain a +1 to the results of skills and defenses","you gain a +1 to the results of attack, defense, and skill checks","epic_relaxed","Epic Relaxed","trait_relaxed",B.ay),A.aA("when you spend a supply, flip a coin. On heads, you don't spend the supply.","whenever you use a [Action], pick a free space adjacent to you or one of the targets, and place a pile of scrap. The pile of scrap counts as a barrier. You may target a pile to make it into a wall of scrap, which is considered a wall. Once on your turn when adjacent to a pile or wall of scrap, you may destroy the scrap and target yourself or an ally range 3, and either gain a supply or give the target a shield, pile {Half Level d6} wall {Half level d12}. Once a turn, as a free action, you may destroy scrap you can see, and deal damage to an enemy adjacent to the scrap, deal {Half level d6} for a pile and {Half Level d12}.","epic_scrapper","Epic Scrapper","trait_scrapper",B.ay),A.aA("once a check, when an ally succeeds on a skill, you may force them to reroll the check and you gain 1 success. The next time you would make the same check, automatically succeed.\nWhen you fail a defense that any of your allies also had to make, you must swap results with an ally who succeeded if possible.","once a turn, when an ally succeeds a check. You can take the success, making them reroll the check. When you would next make that same check, use the success and succeed automatically. When the check is an attack it must include targets from the original attack. When the check is a defense or skill they must be the same specific defense or skill. Unused successes are lost at the end of the encounter.\nWhen you fail a defense that any of your allies also had to make, you must swap results with an ally who succeeded if possible.","epic_self_interested","Epic Self Interest","trait_self_interested",B.ay),A.aA("whenever you would have to make a convince check when with an ally, you may force the ally to make the check instead of you. You have disadvantage on convince checks when alone.","at the start of your turn, if there is no creature adjacent to you, You hide. Whenever you are no longer hidden, dash {Half Level} spaces.","epic_shy","Epic Shy","trait_shy",B.ay),A.aA("every situation, you and each ally character gains 1 reroll for any skill and 1 reroll for any defense.","you have social dice that start each turn as {Half Level d6}. On your turn, each time you become adjacent to an ally for the first time this turn, increase your social dice size once to a max of {Half level d12}. You may allow yourself and any ally you visited to spend your social dice in the following ways.\nWhen dealing damage, spend and add the dice to the damage.\nWhen failing a defense roll, spend and add the dice as shield before taking damage.\nWhen healing or granting shield, increase the amount by the spent dice.\n When you start your turn with unspent social dice, roll them and gain that amount as shield divided between yourself and your visited allies as you wish.","epic_social","Epic Social","trait_social",B.ay),A.aA("whenever you make a defense check, gain 1 skill reroll.","Whenever you are damaged by an attack or status check gain {Level/3 d6} adrenaline dice, if you are below half health gain {Level /3 d12} instead. Whenever you succeed in an attack, you may pay and roll adrenaline dice to give the targets that much extra damage and you gain that much shield. Whenever you are healed or gain shields, you may pay and roll adrenaline to heal or gain that much shield. Whenever an adjacent ally is targeted by an attack that doesn't include you as a target, you are attacked instead. When you succeed on a defense, you may choose to be hit by the attack but take half damage, Resistance is still applied.","epic_thrill_seeker","Epic Thrill Seeker","trait_thrill_seeker",B.ay),A.aA("you have {Half Level} gizmos that you regain at the end of a situation. Each gismo is assigned 2 skills, 1 of which you must be proficient in. A character can use the gismo to gain a +1 to the results of the selected skills. A gismo may be used as a supply.","at the end of the round, Make a create check, on success create a new contraption and keep or give it to any ally whenever they are adjacent. The contraption can be activated as a free action and has the effect of a skill in combat [Action] of your choice with a free supply worth of improvements. You select the bonus when you make the contraption and you must pick a different bonus than you did last round. The contraption last for the situation.","epic_tinkerer","Epic Tinkerer","trait_tinkerer",B.ay),A.aA("Whenever violence could be used to solve a problem rather than another skill, you may roll your attack roll instead. These rolls count as a skill (violence) for the purposes of determining effects.","When you fail an attack, Defense, or skill check, or when you succeed a skill or defense, you must give a creature at range 4, {1d8} Bleed. You may target yourself. When you succeed on an attack that deals damage, roll your current bleed and burn dice and deal that much damage to the targets of the attack ignoring Shield and Resistance.","epic_violent","Epic Violent","trait_violent",B.ay)],A.am("x<ng>"))})
s($,"b7W","tl",()=>A.b([A.cE("Volley: Target a 2 space radius, at the end of the next round, Each creature in the location takes {Half Level d12} Damage.\nOr\nSmoke: Target a 3 space radius, at the end of the next round, smoke fills the space obscuring vision and allowing anyone inside to hide. The smoke last 1 round.","epic_method_artillery","method_artillery","Artillery"),A.cE("Hack: Target 1 enemy. Next round, You and your allies gain +1 Bonus to attack results against the target and defense results caused by the target.\nOr\nOverclock: Target yourself or an ally. They gain a +1 to skill results and at the start of their turn roll 1d6, taking that much damage and may move that may extra spaces on their turn. They may roll up to {Vitality} extra d6 for more extra movement.","epic_method_body_hacker","method_body_hacker","Body Hacker"),A.cE("Burst: Next round, increase the damage of all attacks that deal damage by {Half Level d6}.\nOr\nErupt: Next round, if you miss an attack or end your turn without attacking, target 1 enemy you can see, you and it take {Half Level d6} damage.","epic_method_burst_mage","method_burst_mage","Burst Mage"),A.cE("Snacks: Gain 1 snack that when eaten heals {Half Level d12}. You may use an item interaction to eat a snack or to give an ally one of your snacks. Your allies may use an item interaction to take and eat one snack.\nOr\nMeal: Gain 1 Meal. Meals can be eaten using an [Action] or [Reaction] and heal {Half Level d12} and give {Half Level} d12 regeneration. Whenever you would heal or regenerate, you may instead make a defense to resist an ongoing effect. Your allies may use an [Action] or [Reaction] to eat a meal.","epic_method_chef","method_chef","Chef"),A.cE("Ride: Dash {Level} ignoring Difficult Terrain. Next round you ignore difficult terrain and gain {Half Level} speed.\nGo With the Flow: Gain a +1 to defense results, after you succeed a defense for an attack, you may dash {Half Level} spaces.","epic_method_concrete_surfer","method_concrete_surfer","Concrete Surfer"),A.cE("Death: You must Target a Creature you can see and deal {Half Level d12} Damage to them. You may target yourself.\nOr\nReaper: The next time any creature you can see heals, they do not and instead take {Half Level d6} damage. This may target allies. If an ability targets multiple creature choose randomly.","epic_method_death_weaver","method_death_weaver","Death Weaver"),A.cE("Drone: You gain a drone. When you use an ability using your [Action] or a [Reaction] during your or ally turns, you may use the drone to target the ability from any free space, and gain a +1 to attack & check results.\nOr\nDelivery: You or an ally regains 1 supply.","epic_method_drone","method_drone","Drone"),A.cE("Blaze: Target Yourself or An ally and Deal {Half Level d8} damage to all enemies adjacent to the target. You may also damage the target, and any allies adjacent to the target to increase the damage to {Half Level d12}.\nBurn: Target yourself or a consenting ally, and give them up to {Half Level} d6 burn. While they have this burn, they also gain {Half Level} bonus speed.","epic_method_fire_weaver","method_fire_weaver","Fire Weaver"),A.cE("Weave: Heal {Half Level d6}\nor\nRip: Lose {Half Level d6} health ignoring shield and resistance and deal {Half level d12} extra damage on your next successful attack.\nOr\nWarp: Target a Creature you can see, Teleport to a free space adjacent to the target. For every 3 spaces you teleport take 1d6 damage. If you survive, the target takes the same damage.","epic_method_hemomancer","method_hemomancer","Hemomancer"),A.cE("Frost: Target a 1 space radius and give all enemies there {One Third Level} cold.\nFreeze: Target a free space you can see and summon an ice block as a barrier. [Reaction] Whenever an enemy becomes adjacent to the block during their turn, they gain {One Third Level} cold and the block.","epic_method_ice_weaver","method_ice_weaver","Ice Weaver"),A.cE("Beacon: Target yourself and all allies range 4 and heal {Half Level d6}. At the end of your next turn, repeat the heal.\nOr\nFruit: Target a free space and grow a fruit plant as a barrier. You and your allies may eat the fruit as an item interaction, destroying it and gaining {Half Level} d6 regeneration.","epic_method_life_weaver","method_life_weaver","Life Weaver"),A.cE("Strike: Target each enemy in a 1 space radius and deal {Half Level d6} Damage and knock them prone. If they are already prone, they take {Level d6} damage instead.\nOr\nCharge: Target yourself and each ally in a 1 space radius. On each targets next successful attack, knock the targets prone. If they are already prone, they take {Half Level d6} Damage.","epic_method_lightning_weaver","method_lightning_weaver","Lightning Weaver"),A.cE("Strike: On your next turn, Before or After taking your [Action], Deal {Level d6} damage to 1 enemy range 1. If the Action requires an unarmed hand or hands, deal {Level d10} damage instead.\nOr\nLeg work: Next Round, standing from prone costs you 1 movement (Easy Prone). After succeeding any attack, defense, or skill, you may dash 1 space.","epic_method_martial_artist","method_martial_artist","Martial Artist"),A.cE("Create: Create 1 undead in a free space range 6, up to a max of {Level /3} undead. Undead are 1 health chumps that use your defenses. Whenever an enemy provokes an attack from an undead, they are grappled instead. If a creature ends its turn grappled by an undead, it takes {Level d12} damage. During your turn, you may move each undead 3 spaces.\nOr\nAttack: Move all your undead 3 spaces, and each may grapple 1 enemy in range.","epic_method_necromancer","method_necromancer","Necromancer"),A.cE("Alien Presence: Next Round, the first time each enemy starts their turn or comes within 3 spaces of you during their turn or your turn, they take {Half Level d6} damage of a type and you gain resistance to that type. Pick a defense type when you pick this.\nOr\nUnbound: increase your speed by half, you move through enemies and don't provoke attacks. You have a -1 to all attacks and skills.","epic_method_otherworldly","method_otherworldly","Otherworldly"),A.cE("Missing: Next round, you may not be targeted with attacks until you have finished your turn and during your turn you do not provoke attacks and may move through enemy spaces.\nOr\nThrough: Your attacks this round ignore either resistance or shields, and you have a -1 to defense str and Dex results.","epic_method_phasing","method_phasing","Phasing"),A.cE("Make 1 of the below poison. When you succeed on an attack, spend a poison to cause the targets to gain the effect until the start of your next turn.\nSlow: Reduce their speed by {Half Level}.\nWeaken: You and allies resist damage caused by the target.\nSicken: The target halves all healing and shields.\nDeadly: The targets take {Level /3 d6} extra damage.\nDisable: on a Melee only, Choose a defense, the target has disadvantage on all of the chosen defense.","epic_method_poisoner","method_poisoner","Poisoner"),A.cE("Gain {Vitality d6} Protection. As long as you have Protection, if you or an ally within 3 spaces would take damage, you may lose Protection as if it was Shield. You cannot have more protection than your max shield.","epic_method_protector","method_protector","Protector"),A.cE("Target a 2 space radius range 6 and give each enemy 1 rainbow charge. When you attack an enemy with a rainbow charge, remove one charge and trigger one of the following effects based on the defense targeted by the attack.\nOr\nGain {Level /3} rainbow charges. When you succeed in an attack, trigger a rainbow charge on one target to gain the above effect.\n\nStr: knock the target prone and push them {Half Level} spaces.\nDex: Give the target {Half Level} d6 Bleed.\nVit: Give the target {Half Level} d6 burn.\nInt: deal {Half Level d6} damage to enemies within 2 of the target, excluding the target.\nWis: reduce the target's speed by {Half Level} until the start of your next turn.\nCha: Give an ally range {Level} of the target or you, {Half Level d6} shield.","epic_method_rainbow_weaver","method_rainbow_weaver","Rainbow Weaver"),A.cE("Target yourself or an ally range {Level}, they gain 1 of the following options. For each time a character is targeted by Restorer after the first, they take {Their Vitality} damage.\nRegain {their Power} MP.\nGain 1 Crafting Ingredient.\nRegain the Use of 1 Gadget.\nRegain 1 use of granted power.\nGain 1 Heat, this cannot trigger overheats.\nGain {Their Power} vice.\nGain {Their Vitality or Power} stamina.\nGain {Power} Psi Points.\nReroll 1 Chronomancy dice.\nAdvantage on their next innate ability check.","epic_method_restorer","method_restorer","Restorer"),A.cE("Target 1 enemy and deal {Half Level d10} damage.\nOr\nGain 1 charge of smite, when you succeed on an attack spend a charge to deal {Half Level d10} to the targets of the attack.","epic_method_smite","method_smite","Smite"),A.cE("Gain 1 Training until the end of the situation. You may spend 1 training to trigger a Weapon Technique Reaction you know. During your turn you may spend 1 training to end burning, bleeding, prone or to reroll a defense to resist an ongoing effect.","epic_method_soldier","method_soldier","Soldier"),A.cE("Passive: Start with 1 soul shard. At the end of the round, if at least 1 character died that round, gain 1 soul shard. You lose all soul shards at the end of the encounter. Taking soul shard generating methods multiple times doesn\u2019t increase the number of shards you gain per round or start with.\nWhen Triggered: Gain {Soul Shards d6} shield and Either, pull an enemy you can see {2*Soul Shards} spaces, or force an enemy you can see to move {Soul Shard} Spaces.\nDestroy Soul Shard: At the end of an enemy\u2019s turn, if you can see the enemy, Either, Pull them {2x Soul Shards} spaces or force them to move {Soul Shards} spaces then lose 1 Soul Shard.","epic_method_soul_adorn","method_soul_adorn","Soul Adorn"),A.cE("Passive: Start with 1 soul shard. At the end of the round, if at least 1 character died that round, gain 1 soul shard. You lose all soul shards at the end of the encounter. Taking soul shard generating methods multiple times doesn\u2019t increase the number of shards you gain per round or start with.\nWhen Triggered: Gain {Soul Shard} d6 Regeneration. Overhealing from this regeneration is gained as shield.\nDestroy Soul Shard: After taking damage, you may heal {Soul Shard d6} then lose 1 soul shard. You must survive the attack to use this.","epic_method_soul_feaster","method_soul_feaster","Soul Feaster"),A.cE("Passive: Start with 1 soul shard. At the end of the round, if at least 1 character died that round, gain 1 soul shard. You lose all soul shards at the end of the encounter. Taking soul shard generating methods multiple times doesn\u2019t increase the number of shards you gain per round or start with.\nWhen Triggered: Next Round, all your attacks deal {Soul Shards d6} extra damage, if the target is Prone, Restrained, Disabled, or Stunned, deal {Soul Shards d8} instead.\nDestroy Soul: After Succeeding an Attack that doesn\u2019t have the benefit of your soul reaper. Deal extra damage as if you had triggered your soul reaper, then lose 1 soul shard.\n\nYou lose all soul shards at the end of the encounter. Taking soul shard generating methods multiple times doesn\u2019t increase the number of shards you gain on kill or start with.","epic_method_soul_reaper","method_soul_reaper","Soul Reaper"),A.cE("Place a Spore in a free space within 3 spaces. When a Creature enters a space with a Spore, Remove the spore and If Enemy: Deal {Half Level d6} Damage. If Ally: Heal {Half Level d6}.\nOr\nPlace a spore on yourself or an ally. When the target succeeds an attack or defense, you may remove the spore and deal {Level / 3 d6} damage to enemies adjacent to the target and heal allies adjacent to the target the same amount.","epic_method_spore_spreader","method_spore_spreader","Spore Spreader"),A.cE("Teleport to a free space within {Level}. Next round, you may teleport up to your speed instead of moving.","epic_method_stride","method_stride","Stride"),A.cE("Either Summon: Place a Summon into a free space within 6. Then any enemy adjacent to at least 1 Summon takes {Half Level d6} damage. Summons last until the end of the encounter or until hit with an attack. They use your defenses and block characters as if they were a player. On your turn, you may use your [Reaction] to move all your summons 6 spaces, and make an Melee Attack. On Success, Deal {Half Level d6} to each enemy adjacent to at least 1 summon. When you pick this, choose what defense their attacks target.\nOr Attack:  Move all your summons 6 spaces, and any enemy adjacent to at least 1 Summon takes {Half Level d6} damage.","epic_method_summoner","method_summoner","Summoner"),A.cE("Next Round, if you have advantage on an attack or at least 1 ally adjacent to the target of an attack that deals damage, Deal {Half Level d8} extra damage.\nOr\nMove {Level/3} then hide.","epic_method_unfair_attacker","method_unfair_attacker","Unfair Attacker"),A.cE("Next round, Before or After your [Action], Target an enemy with a weapon you are holding and make a Weapon Attack with a source value of {level}\nOr\nGain 1 resolve. The next time you miss a weapon attack, spend 1 resolve and reroll the attack. If you then succeed, gain {Half Level d6} Shield.","epic_method_warrior","method_warrior","Warrior"),A.cE("Rain: Target a 1 space radius and each enemy there becomes Soggy until the end of the next round. While soggy, You and Your allies deal {Half Level d6} Damage whenever they Succeed with an Attack or Status Check that deals damage against the target.\nOr\nWater: gain 1 water, when you succeed an attack, spend 1 water to give all targets soggy until the start of your next turn.","epic_method_water_weaver","method_water_weaver","Water Weaver"),A.cE("Grow: Target 1 space and turn the ground there into weeds for the rest of the encounter. The weeds are difficult terrain for your enemies. You may target Melee attacks from the location of the weeds.\nOr\nTangle: Gain 1 plant, when you succeed a Melee attack, spend 1 plant and choose 1 of the targets, placing a weed in one of their spaces and restraining them until the start of your next turn.","epic_method_weed_weaver","method_weed_weaver","Weed Weaver"),A.cE("Breeze: Target yourself and up to {Half Level} other creatures and force them to dash up to {Level} spaces all in the same direction.\nOr\nGust: Gain 1 wind charge, When you succeed an attack, spend a wind charge and force the targets and yourself to dash up to {Level} spaces all in the same direction.","epic_method_wind_weaver","method_wind_weaver","Wind Weaver")],A.am("x<kw>")))
r($,"b8l","tn",()=>{var q="If you are currently High gain Fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune. Your addiction must cost 1 supply to use and requires use of your Action or Reaction to get high. You remain high for the remainder of the situation. Pick 1 skill, and gain disadvantage on all checks with it while high. Pick one of the below mods for your addiction.\n\nQuick: During Combat, Use an Item interaction instead of a reaction or action. Adventuring, When you roll the trait, you may get high immediately by paying 2 supplies instead of one.\nStrong: Gain 2 fortunes when high and 2 Misfortunes when not.\nHomemade: Your drug doesn\u2019t cost supply, when used roll Create, on failure lose Hp equal to your {vitality d6}. Regardless, you are high.",p="Flip a coin, on Heads gain Fortune on Tails gain Misfortune.",o="You gain Misfortune. The next time one of your allies would gain Misfortune, they instead gain nothing. Your Misfortune credit lasts until it is used, and you may have any number of credits. You may not use a Misfortune credit on another Giving trait.",n="Your keepsake is an object that is always on your person. Whenever you fail a Dex Defense, you drop your keepsake. If your keepsake is destroyed or lost, after the situation you may repair or remake your keepsake and you have 1 less supply in your next situation. If you have your keepsake you gain fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune.",m="Gain Fortune, the next time one of your allies would gain fortune, they instead do not. This fortune debt lasts until it's paid, and the party may owe multiple fortunes. You may not pay the Fortune debt using another Self Interested Trait. Giving credits and Self Interest debts do not cancel each other."
return A.b([A.eK(q,q,"epic_addict","trait_addict","Addict"),A.eK("If you succeed on your next check in the situation, gain fortune, otherwise gain misfortune.","If you Succeeded on your action, gain Fortune, otherwise gain misfortune. If you didn\u2019t make a check, ignore.","epic_confidence","trait_confidence","Confidence"),A.eK("if you are doing an involved task, gain fortune, otherwise gain misfortune. You must have an ability that requires concentration to take Distractible.","If you are concentrating, gain Fortune, Otherwise gain Misfortune.","epic_distractible","trait_distractible","Distractible"),A.eK("If you forget something gain fortune otherwise gain misfortune.","If you didn't use your [action], or [Reaction] or forgot to use one of your abilities, gain fortune, otherwise gain misfortune.","epic_forgetful","trait_forgetful","Forgetful"),A.eK(p,p,"epic_gambler","trait_gambler","Gambler"),A.eK(o,o,"epic_giving","trait_giving","Giving"),A.eK("If you are helping an ally gain fortune, otherwise gain misfortune.","If you targeted an ally with an ability, gain Fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune.","epic_helpful","trait_helpful","Helpful"),A.eK("If the situation was caused by following your plan Gain Misfortune, otherwise Gain Fortune.","During your turn, If you use a different action than you did on your last turn, gain Fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune. Ignore in the first round.","epic_impulsive","trait_impulsive","Impulsive"),A.eK(n,n,"epic_keepsake","trait_keepsake","Keepsake"),A.eK("If the situation was caused by following your plan, gain Fortune, Otherwise gain Misfortune.","make a plan of what you are going to do with your action and bonus on your next turn. If you do exactly that and do not take the first turn, gain fortune otherwise gain Misfortune.","epic_planner","trait_planner","Planner"),A.eK("When in a dangerous situation gain Misfortune. Otherwise Gain Fortune.","If you were attacked this round or have taken damage, gain Misfortune, Otherwise gain Fortune.","epic_nervous","trait_nervous","Nervous"),A.eK("if your actions caused the situation gain fortune otherwise gain misfortune.","if you used your reaction, gain fortune. Otherwise gain misfortune.","epic_reactive","trait_reactive","Reactive"),A.eK("if your actions didn't directly cause the situation gain fortune otherwise misfortune.","If you haven't used your reaction, gain fortune. Otherwise gain misfortune.","epic_relaxed","trait_relaxed","Relaxed"),A.eK("Regain a supply and gain a Misfortune.","If you used an object interaction to loot, gain fortune, otherwise gain misfortune.","epic_scrapper","trait_scrapper","Scrapper"),A.eK(m,m,"epic_self_interested","trait_self_interested","Self Interested"),A.eK("If you are hidden or not engaged, Gain Fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune.","If no character is adjacent to you, gain Fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune.","epic_shy","trait_shy","Shy"),A.eK("If you aren\u2019t Hidden or you are Engaged with a character, Gain Fortune. Otherwise gain Misfortune.","If you have an ally Adjacent to you, gain Fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune.","epic_social","trait_social","Social"),A.eK("If in a Dangerous situation gain Fortune. Otherwise Gain Misfortune.","If you were attacked this round, Gain Fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune.","epic_thrill_seeker","trait_thrill_seeker","Thrill Seeker"),A.eK("gain a misfortune and the first 2 times you would use supply in this situation you do not use supply.","If you didn\u2019t use your object interaction, gain Fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune.","epic_tinkerer","trait_tinkerer","Tinkerer"),A.eK("If the situation was caused by violence gain Fortune otherwise gain Misfortune.","If you made an attack, gain Fortune, otherwise gain Misfortune.","epic_violent","trait_violent","Violent")],A.am("x<kx>"))})
